Package: wtf
Version: @VERSION@
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Anurag Bhaskarya <anuragbhaskarya@gmail.com>
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.15), bash (>= 4.0)
Recommends: sudo
Homepage: https://github.com/AnuragBhaskarya/wtf
Description: A lightning-fast command-line dictionary tool for Linux
 WTF is a command-line dictionary tool that helps you
 look up and manage definitions right from your terminal.
 Simple, fast, and easy to use!
 .
 Features:
  * Quick term lookup with case-insensitive search
  * Add and manage custom definitions
  * Local storage in user's home directory
  * Auto-update capability
  * Recovery feature for removed definitions